Wrapping up the implementation of the data members or methods inside a class -  basic definition
It hides the code and other data members into a single entity so that it can be protected from outside world

Encapsulation is a implementation level concept, it focuses in the internal working of the code
It basically bundles the properties in the class

Data Hiding focuses on the security of the instance variable.
whereas Encapsulation focuses on hiding the complexity of the system

Encapsulation is the sub process in doing data hiding.